SANBERN v. WRIGHT & COBB LIGHTERAGE CO. (two cases). (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 14, 1910.) No. 285. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Wray & Callaghan and Nelson Keach, for appellant. Kneeland & Harison, for appellee.

Before LACOMBE, WARD, and NOYES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed on, opinion of District Judge (171 Fed. 449), with interest and costs.
